\title{Convergence: The March 27 Collision}
\taxon{chronicle}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-04}
\tag{sessions}
\tag{convergence}

\import{macros}
\meta{institution}{BCI Factory}

\p{On March 27, 2026, seven simultaneous Claude sessions — 478 messages total — converged on the same intent: launching BCI Factory. None completed. All died. What survived became this forest.}

\subtree{
\title{The Seven Sessions}

\table{
  \tr{\th{#} \th{Session ID} \th{Messages} \th{Attempted} \th{Death}}
  \tr{\td{1} \td{\code{284ddcff}} \td{~70} \td{Beeper coordination — messaging across Signal/Discord/iMessage to rally people to 222 Dore} \td{"ok"}}
  \tr{\td{2} \td{\code{683c9a71}} \td{~65} \td{Domain registration — bcifactory.io, bcifactory.org, bci.horse DNS} \td{"ok ok ok"}}
  \tr{\td{3} \td{\code{332e513c}} \td{~80} \td{MCP infrastructure — wiring gay-mcp, beeper-mcp, google-workspace into unified agent stack} \td{mid-sentence override}}
  \tr{\td{4} \td{\code{83be562e}} \td{~55} \td{Device procurement — OpenBCI Cyton ordering, Cognionics Quick-30 rental, HackEEG sourcing} \td{context exhaustion}}
  \tr{\td{5} \td{\code{8f1d7cef}} \td{~70} \td{SvelteKit site — Three.js floor plan of 250 Dore, hardware table, responsive layout} \td{"ok"}}
  \tr{\td{6} \td{\code{33f6e944}} \td{~60} \td{Forester forest — initial tree structure, macros, bcf/bci/horse prefix taxonomy} \td{token limit}}
  \tr{\td{7} \td{\code{3c3bf3cf}} \td{~78} \td{EEG headset connection — Cyton dongle physically connected, BrainFlow streaming, channel validation} \td{dongle disconnected}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Convergent Intent}

\p{All seven sessions were attempting the same thing from different angles:}

\ol{
  \li{\strong{Beeper coordination} — get humans to the physical space}
  \li{\strong{EEG headset connection} — get hardware streaming data}
  \li{\strong{bcifactory.io domain} — get a public address}
  \li{\strong{Device procurement} — get more hardware into the space}
  \li{\strong{MCP infrastructure} — get agents wired to tools}
}

\p{The convergence was not planned. Seven threads launched independently within hours of each other, each pulling toward the same attractor: a place where you sit down and see your brain.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Session #7 Was Closest}

\p{Session \code{3c3bf3cf} got furthest. The OpenBCI Cyton dongle (USB serial \code{DP05IU8D}) was physically plugged in. BrainFlow initialized. Channels 1–8 showed impedance values. The synthetic board fallback confirmed the pipeline worked end to end.}

\p{Then the dongle disconnected — physically. A cable got bumped. The session died trying to reconnect. The actual EEG capture came four days later, on March 31 ([[bcf-0040]]).}
}

\subtree{
\title{What Died}

\p{478 messages of context. Seven independent attempts at the same thing. Hours of agent-human coordination. All of it — gone when the sessions ended.}

\p{What survived: the \em{artifacts} each session produced before dying ([[bcf-0039]]). Files on disk. Trees in the forest. Code in repos. The sessions are dead. The forest is alive.}
}
